h1 Where's the caret? üßê
p.
  Ever needed to determine the caret position? It's useful to know when you want to show custom UI at the exact location a user is interacting with a form.<br/>
  Common use cases are UI using typeaheads and content highlighting within WYSIWYG environments.
p.
  Experiment with the elements below!
h2 Show caret position on input and click
.demo-input
  .input__wrapper.get-position-input
    .input__marker.input__marker--position Here's the caret!
    input.input(id='positionInput', placeholder='Interact with me')
.demo-input
  .input__wrapper.get-position-textarea
    .input__marker.input__marker--position Here's the caret!
    textarea.input(id='positionTextarea', placeholder='Interact with me')
